-- U.S. top court rules against Argentina in bonds discovery case
-- By Lawrence Hurley
-- Mon Jun 16, 2014 10:17AM EDT
-- None



WASHINGTON, June 16 (Reuters) - The U.S. Supreme Court on Monday ruled that creditors can seek information about Argentina's non-U.S. assets in a case about bank subpoenas that is part of the decade-long litigation over Argentina's obligations to bond investors.

